; Partial Revisions * [[July 18, 1907]] (Imperial Ordinance No. 280 of Meiji 40): ** Updated admission requirements to align with the extended {{ill|Compulsory education|en|Compulsory education|qid=Q511009|lt=Compulsory education|1=Compulsory education}} term<ref>Mandatory education was extended from four years (Jinjo Shōgakkō) to six years under the [[Shōgakkōrei]] revision.</ref>. ** Required graduates of six-year Jinjo Shōgakkō for Chūgakkō admission. * [[February 7, 1919]] (Imperial Ordinance No. 11 of Taishō 8): ** Expanded authority for school associations to establish Chūgakkō. ** Allowed establishment of preparatory courses ({{ill|Yoka|en|Yoka|qid=Q20661847|lt=Yoka|1=Yoka}}) within Chūgakkō for students meeting elementary school equivalency criteria. ** "Regulations for Enforcement of Chūgakkōrei" (March 29, 1919) set preparatory course term at two years for students aged 10 or older. * [[March 1, 1941]] (Imperial Ordinance No. 151 of Shōwa 16): ** Amended admission requirements to align with [[Kokumin Gakkō]] under the [[Kokumin Gakkōrei]].
